# VPG Engine — Hierarchical Finite State Machine Blueprint

## Combat Systems Architecture — Formal Specification

---

## 1. TOP-LEVEL STATE REGIONS

The character controller is decomposed into four concurrent regions. Two are **exclusive** (only one child state active at a time). Two are **orthogonal** (always ticking in parallel with the exclusive regions).

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    CHARACTER ROOT                        │
│                                                         │
│  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │
│  │   ACTION REGION      │  │   SPIRIT METER REGION   │  │
│  │   (exclusive)        │  │   (orthogonal)          │  │
│  │                      │  │                         │  │
│  │  The primary FSM.    │  │  Tracks momentum value, │  │
│  │  Governs what the    │  │  spirit tier, Special   │  │
│  │  character is doing  │  │  activation, and decay. │  │
│  │  at any given frame. │  │  Reads events from      │  │
│  │                      │  │  Action region.         │  │
│  │  One active state    │  │  Never blocks or gates  │  │
│  │  at all times.       │  │  Action transitions     │  │
│  │                      │  │  directly — only        │  │
│  │                      │  │  exposes queryable      │  │
│  │                      │  │  flags.                 │  │
│  └──────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────┘  │
│                                                         │
│  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │
│  │   BODY DAMAGE REGION │  │   INTERACTION REGION    │  │
│  │   (orthogonal)       │  │   (exclusive)           │  │
│  │                      │  │                         │  │
│  │  Per-body-part HP    │  │  Manages paired states  │  │
│  │  tracking. Receives  │  │  between two characters │  │
│  │  damage events from  │  │  during grapple locks,  │  │
│  │  Action region.      │  │  pins, submissions.     │  │
│  │  Feeds thresholds    │  │  Owns the "who is       │  │
│  │  back (KO eligible,  │  │  attacker / defender"   │  │
│  │  bleed triggered,    │  │  relationship.          │  │
│  │  limping, etc).      │  │                         │  │
│  │                      │  │  Idle when character is │  │
│  │                      │  │  acting solo.           │  │
│  └──────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────┘  │
│                                                         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Region Classification

| Region | Type | Justification |
|--------|------|---------------|
| **Action** | Exclusive | A character does exactly one thing per frame: idle, moving, striking, grappling, downed, rising, etc. Mutual exclusion enforced by the FSM itself. |
| **Spirit Meter** | Orthogonal | Momentum accumulates and decays regardless of current action. Must tick every frame independently. Not a "state" the character is "in" — it is a continuous resource with thresholds. |
| **Body Damage** | Orthogonal | Damage to head, body, arms, legs tracks independently of what the character is doing. A character can be in Idle with 80% head damage. This is persistent data, not a behavioral state. |
| **Interaction** | Exclusive | When two characters are locked together (grapple hold, pin, submission), a shared interaction context exists. Exactly one interaction or none. This region is dormant during solo action. |

### Why This Decomposition

The AKI engine runs on a model where the spirit meter, body damage, and the action state machine are all independent systems that feed data to each other but never share ownership of transitions. A grapple doesn't "live inside" the spirit meter. The spirit meter doesn't "own" the finisher execution. They communicate through event dispatch and flag queries. This decomposition preserves that.

