## 3. STATE RESPONSIBILITY RULES

### Neutral

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Movement vector calculation, facing update, proximity checks for grapple range, input polling for A/B/R/C-Down/Control Stick, block state toggle |
| **Logic NOT here** | Damage application, move execution, spirit meter updates |
| **Entry events** | `MOVE_COMPLETE`, `RISING_COMPLETE`, `REVERSAL_COMPLETE`, `TAUNT_COMPLETE`, `MATCH_START` |
| **Exit events** | `GRAPPLE_ATTEMPT` → GrappleInitiation, `STRIKE_INPUT` → Striking, `HIT_RECEIVED` → Stunned/Downed, `RUN_INPUT` → Running, `TAUNT_INPUT` → Taunt |
| **Guards** | Cannot transition to GrappleInitiation if already in hit stun. Cannot transition to Running if cornered against ropes with no room. |

### Striking

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Strike type resolution (arm vs leg based on distance, weak vs strong based on hold duration), hitbox activation on defined frame, hit evaluation against defender state |
| **Logic NOT here** | Grapple slot lookup, spirit tier management, ground interaction |
| **Entry events** | `STRIKE_INPUT` from Neutral or Running |
| **Exit events** | `STRIKE_COMPLETE` → Neutral, `STRIKE_BLOCKED` → Neutral (attacker stagger), `STRIKE_REVERSED` → Stunned (attacker becomes defender) |
| **Guards** | Cannot initiate strong strike if opponent is in iframes (rising invincibility). Running strikes only valid from Running substate. |

### GrappleInitiation

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Proximity gate check (are characters within grapple range?), facing gate check (front or back?), hold duration measurement (tap vs hold A), result: success → GrappleHold, fail → whiff animation → Neutral |
| **Logic NOT here** | Move slot resolution (that happens in GrappleHold), damage, spirit changes |
| **Entry events** | `GRAPPLE_ATTEMPT` with proximity + facing passing guard |
| **Exit events** | `GRAPPLE_CONNECTED` → GrappleHold, `GRAPPLE_WHIFFED` → Neutral (short recovery), `GRAPPLE_EVADED` → Neutral (opponent dodged) |
| **Guards** | Target must be in a grappable state (Neutral.Idle, Neutral.Walking, Stunned.Dazed, Stunned.BarricadeLean). Target must NOT be: Downed, Rising, already in GrappleHold, in ExecutingMove, in iframes. Proximity must be ≤ `GRAPPLE_RANGE` constant. |

### GrappleHold

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Hold type classification (front/back × weak/strong × position context), input window countdown (attacker has N frames to input direction+button), slot resolution on input (direction + button → slot ID), reversal window for defender (polled each frame), hold timeout (no input → grapple breaks), L-button position switch (front↔back, limited count), R-button grapple break |
| **Logic NOT here** | Move execution (that happens in ExecutingMove after slot resolves), damage application |
| **Entry events** | `GRAPPLE_CONNECTED` from GrappleInitiation |
| **Exit events** | `SLOT_RESOLVED` → ExecutingMove, `HOLD_TIMEOUT` → Neutral (both), `GRAPPLE_REVERSED` → Reversal (defender) + Stunned (attacker), `HOLD_BROKEN` → Neutral (both), `POSITION_SWITCHED` → re-enter GrappleHold with flipped front/back |
| **Guards** | Finisher slot only resolves if SpiritMeter.isSpecialActive() is true for attacker. Position switch limited to max N times per hold. Cannot switch while reversal window is resolving. |

### ExecutingMove

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Frame counter tick against `move.totalFrames` from JSON, hit evaluation on `move.impactFrame`, damage dispatch to BodyDamage region on impact, KO/bleed evaluation against BodyDamage thresholds, feature evaluation (Pin → PinAttempt, Submit → SubmissionAttempt), spirit meter events (attacker gains, defender loses/gains based on move and spirit system rules) |
| **Logic NOT here** | Input polling (locked out during execution), animation control (presentation layer syncs to frame counter), grapple initiation |
| **Entry events** | `SLOT_RESOLVED` from GrappleHold, or `STRIKE_EXECUTING` from Striking |
| **Exit events** | `MOVE_COMPLETE` → Neutral (attacker) + Downed/Stunned (defender based on move properties), `MOVE_PIN` → PinAttempt, `MOVE_SUBMIT` → SubmissionAttempt |
| **Guards** | Cannot be entered without a valid move ID. Frame counter must not exceed `move.totalFrames`. |

### IrishWhip

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Whip direction vector, rope bounce physics, rebound timing, follow-up window for whipper (B for strike, A for grapple catch, Control Stick for finisher if strong whip + Special), corner counter detection if target reaches turnbuckle |
| **Logic NOT here** | Standard grapple slot resolution, ground game |
| **Entry events** | `IRISH_WHIP_INITIATED` from GrappleHold (L-button whip) |
| **Exit events** | `WHIP_FOLLOWUP_STRIKE` → Striking, `WHIP_FOLLOWUP_GRAPPLE` → GrappleHold (IrishWhipHold subtype), `WHIP_TO_CORNER` → Stunned.BarricadeLean or CornerSlump (defender), `WHIP_NO_FOLLOWUP` → Neutral (both) |
| **Guards** | Follow-up window has fixed frame count. If window expires, both return to Neutral. Corner counter requires defender input during specific frame window. |

### Downed

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Get-up timer (auto-rise after N frames based on spirit tier and body damage), substate classification (face up, face down, sitting up, sitting down — determined by the move that caused the knockdown), vulnerability flags for opponent ground interactions |
| **Logic NOT here** | Active input resolution (downed character has no offensive options), grapple logic, striking logic |
| **Entry events** | `KNOCKDOWN` from ExecutingMove or Striking, `FLYING_ATTACK_MISS` from Aerial |
| **Exit events** | `RISE_TIMER_EXPIRED` → Rising, `OPPONENT_GROUND_GRAPPLE` → GroundInteraction (as defender), `OPPONENT_PIN` → PinAttempt, `OPPONENT_PICKUP` → Neutral (standing, dazed) |
| **Guards** | Cannot rise before minimum downed frames. Rise speed scales with spirit tier. Cannot be pinned during Falling substate (must be fully Prone). |

### Rising

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Rise animation frame counter, iframes during first N frames of rise, R-hold detection for RecoveringAttack branch, spirit-based kip-up availability |
| **Logic NOT here** | Standard movement, grapple initiation, striking |
| **Entry events** | `RISE_TIMER_EXPIRED` from Downed |
| **Exit events** | `RISE_COMPLETE` → Neutral, `RECOVERING_ATTACK_INPUT` → Striking (ducking attack slot), `HIT_DURING_RISE` → Downed (if after iframes expire) |
| **Guards** | RecoveringAttack only fires if R was held before rise began. Kip-up only available if SpiritMeter tier ≥ Hot. |

### PinAttempt

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Count progression (1, 2, 3), kickout check per count (defender mashes, difficulty scaled by body damage + spirit tier), referee position tracking, rope break detection |
| **Logic NOT here** | Move execution, standard striking, grapple initiation |
| **Entry events** | `MOVE_PIN` from ExecutingMove, or manual pin input near downed opponent |
| **Exit events** | `PIN_SUCCESS` → MatchManager (win condition), `KICKOUT` → Rising (defender) + Neutral (attacker), `ROPE_BREAK` → Neutral (both) |
| **Guards** | Cannot pin if opponent is not in valid Downed substate. Cannot pin outside ring in standard match. Rope break auto-triggers if defender's position overlaps rope hitbox. |

### SubmissionAttempt

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Hold strength decay/build (attacker mashes to tighten, defender mashes to escape), escape threshold (based on body part damage to targeted limb + spirit tier), tap-out threshold, rope break detection |
| **Logic NOT here** | Everything else |
| **Entry events** | `MOVE_SUBMIT` from ExecutingMove |
| **Exit events** | `SUBMISSION_SUCCESS` → MatchManager (win condition), `ESCAPE_SUBMISSION` → Rising (defender) + Neutral (attacker), `ROPE_BREAK` → Neutral (both) |
| **Guards** | Same pin guards apply. Submission difficulty scales with specific body part damage (a leg submission is harder to escape if leg damage is high). |

### Stunned

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Stun duration countdown (frames), vulnerability flags (grappable, strikeable, pushable), surface-type response routing (BarricadeLean, BalanceStruggle, Dazed) |
| **Logic NOT here** | Offensive input, movement |
| **Entry events** | `HIT_RECEIVED` (light), `GRAPPLE_REVERSED` (attacker becomes stunned), `COLLISION_SURFACE` (barricade, edge) |
| **Exit events** | `STUN_EXPIRED` → Neutral, `HIT_DURING_STUN` → Downed (if threshold exceeded), `GRAPPLED_WHILE_STUNNED` → GrappleHold (as defender) |
| **Guards** | Stun duration cannot be shortened by input. BalanceStruggle can only transition to Falling if struck from behind. |

### Aerial

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Turnbuckle climb frame counter, top rope perch state (taunt available, attack available, opponent counter-grapple window), launch trajectory (standing target vs downed target vs outside target), Special override for flying finisher |
| **Logic NOT here** | Ground grapple, standard striking |
| **Entry events** | `CLIMB_TURNBUCKLE` from Neutral (near corner, D-Pad + C-Down) |
| **Exit events** | `FLYING_ATTACK_HIT` → ExecutingMove, `FLYING_ATTACK_MISS` → Downed (FlyingAttackMiss → Falling), `FLYING_COUNTER_GRAPPLED` → Stunned (countered by opponent), `CLIMB_DOWN` → Neutral |
| **Guards** | Cannot launch if no valid target (target must be in range and in a valid state). Flying finisher only if SpiritMeter.isSpecialActive(). Opponent can counter-grapple only during OnTopRope state within defined frame window. |

### Taunt

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Logic here** | Taunt animation frame counter, spirit meter boost event dispatch, slot resolution (Control Stick direction → taunt slot 1/2/3), Special taunt override |
| **Logic NOT here** | Offensive actions, defensive actions |
| **Entry events** | `TAUNT_INPUT` from Neutral |
| **Exit events** | `TAUNT_COMPLETE` → Neutral, `HIT_DURING_TAUNT` → Stunned (taunts are interruptible) |
| **Guards** | Cannot taunt while in any non-Neutral state. Special taunt only if SpiritMeter.isSpecialActive(). |

